details.description: Specialty coffee shop offering a bistro menu, crafted gifts, wine room, & a bit of New England finds. Private & corporate catering options. We also boast a beautiful event space at the shop for corporate dinners, gatherings, baby showers, wedding rehearsal dinners, birthdays, and more.

reviews_data.review_text:
I’m thrilled to have stumbled across this cozy little spot through the goodie bag app,  where you never quite know what you’ll get—but that’s the fun of it, right? My bag had scratch-made apple cake, a few other baked treats, and some serious charm. Unlike some folks, I didn’t bring a microscope or a grudge.

Let’s just say I enjoyed it more than someone who thinks $7 gets you a  flawless French patisserie experience.

PS: Shoutout to Ricardo at Scott Clark Toyota—apparently the only person in the greater Charlotte area to survive a Vivian review unscathed. 🫣😂
Green mold on the Apple cake.
Such a cute spot! Came here to work for a little bit in between appointments. Kind staff and comfortable seating. Will definitely be coming back!

A spacious and welcoming café with excellent cappuccinos and delicious homemade cookies. The friendly host shared the fascinating history behind the place, adding a personal touch to the visit. They offer a diverse selection of products, including wines and freshly made sandwiches. There’s also a designated area for working on a laptop, making it a great spot for both relaxation and productivity. Highly recommended!
Absolutely lovely. Clean and bright with comfortable seating. Fun gift items. Delicious food and beverages. Can’t wait to return for coffee and wine. Amazing service.

Large space, pretty and uncluttered... Can't hurt to have a couple more 2 to 4 person tables that are not high tops.
Good dark roast coffee.
Cheese in Caesar Salad is good (boxed to-go)
Nice looking croissant on the shelf, will try it next time!
Wine closet (about 30% full, so I'm sure it'll grow)
Access from behind Sleep number store, or road near Cookout
reviews_data.owner_answer:
We appreciate your detailed feedback and are glad you enjoyed our space and food. We would love to serve you again and show you our seating area that’s on the other side of the retail wall. We have a counter top table as well for those that want to bring their laptop! 

 Sincerely, Sweet Pea's Specialty Food Shop.

reviews_data.review_text: The food is so delicious, made from scratch that day! The coffee selection is amazing! When you walk inside, it's stunning! Iwas shocked from the plain shopping mall exterior. Pineville should really do some upgrades. Inside is The perfect place for any and every occasion! Even nice if you want to work at coffee Cafe by a local owner! They even have a wine room and goods from the owners sisters farm in Maine! Best place to buy real maple syrup!
Super cute little shop! Loved my experience, food was delicious!
Incredible coffee and delicious food. Highly recommend!
Awesome place for events! Great coffee! A variety of Pastries!

My daughter and I had the most amazing Mommy-Daughter Date at Sweet Pea’s! This wonderful Cafe and Specialty Shop specializes in homemade baked goods and cafe entrees using locally sourced ingredients as well as specialty treats from Maine. The owner and culinary chef, Rachel, and her staff are an absolute delight, making our experience even more memorable. The food was truly amazing! From the Kitchen Sink Delight Truffle Dessert, to my favorite - the Fruity Chicken Salad, the Sugar Cookie Latte, the Customizable Charcuterie Board, and the Maine Whoopie Pie - every bite was a taste of bliss! I’m so excited for Rachel and her team! Whether you’re looking for a tasty bite and latte, a glass of wine paired with a cute cheese, cracker and meat spread, or need catering for your next party/ event, you’ll be thrilled with Sweet Pea’s delectable quality cuisine. Don’t miss out on this hidden!

Sweet Peas is a great place to stop for breakfast, lunch and a snack and coffee. You can grab a charcuterie cup to go or get a bottle of wine and browse the great selection of cooking and entertaining accessories. You must try the banana pudding cupcake. It’s been a family favorite for years!

How cute is this place!! Huge selection of gifts and snacks, perfect for a girls day lunch. They were advertising a bunch of upcoming events for kids or date night. We met the owner and she was too sweet - fitting for the name haha.
Stumbled across this hidden gem in Pineville. Great coffee and scones.  Will definitely come back for the build your own charcuterie. Super clean.
Great new place in the area. Coffee, breakfast/brunch and mimosas ❤️ stop by before it becomes famous and packed!
Awesome food and very friendly staff!

Had a lovely evening at Sweet Peas! We were genuinely welcomed from the moment we walked inside to the time we bid farewell . The team members are enthusiastic and extraordinarily polite. The space is absolutely stunning! One must take a moment  to view the fused glass panes created by the owners Mom! Every aspect of this Specialty Food Shop is well thought out ! The charcuterie was delightful! From the various cheese options, to the prosciutto, olives, fruit, and seasoned nuts there truly was something for everyone! I had the pleasure of enjoying an iced pumpkin macchiato! This beverage had excellent balance not too pumpkin not too spiced, just the perfect sip of fall ! If you are in need of  seasonal  and specialty food items for hosting this is the spot to be! Hands down the one of the best selection of charcuterie boards with varying shapes and sizes. We look forward to our next visit to have lunch, a specialty beverage and stock up on items for entertaining guests this holiday season!
Sweet Pea’s offered Easter pre orders and it was delicious! Lots of options and Rachel was great to work with! It made Easter dinner a lot easier with the work load off me!
